This paper presents a specialized neural engine that accelerates the computation of convolution layers in deep convolutional neural networks while reducing computational energy. The paper focuses on the optimization of convolutional layers, which is a key component of computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and compression techniques, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also presents a hardware implementation of the proposed method, which is relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Hamming Weight Compressors, which is relevant to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
